dict.string: Subaru’s most important nameplate arrives as a trim level on the newly redesigned Legacy wagon, wearing standard two-tone paint with a gray lower section to suggest plastic body cladding. The idea is more fully fleshed out for ’96, with an increased ride height, raised roof, and large front fog lights; the Outback at that point is marketed as its own model. Given a hefty push from that famous Australian, Crocodile Dundee, sales take off. Subaru even adds an Outback sedan, but it’s the wagon that’s magic.
